From Wiktionary, the free dictionary
See also: stahl and stáhl

English

[edit]

Proper noun

[edit]

Stahl (plural Stahls)

  1. A surname.

Anagrams

[edit]
  • halts, lasht, laths, shalt, sthal

German

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Middle High German stahel, from Old High German stahal, from Proto-Germanic *stahlą, *stahliją. Cognate with Dutch staal, Danish stål, Icelandic stál, also English steel.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ʃtaːl/
  • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)
  • Rhymes: -aːl

Noun

[edit]

Stahl m (strong, genitive Stahles or Stahls, plural Stähle or Stahle)

  1. steel

Declension

[edit]
Declension of Stahl [masculine, strong]
singular plural
indef. def. noun def. noun
nominative ein der Stahl die Stähle, Stahle
genitive eines des Stahles, Stahls der Stähle, Stahle
dative einem dem Stahl, Stahle1 den Stählen, Stahlen
accusative einen den Stahl die Stähle, Stahle

1Now rare, see notes.
